HEADWORD: donnish
<hw>donnish</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>like a university don; marked by a
narrow focus on or display of learning, especially its trivial
aspects.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> academic, pedantic, bookish.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

